## Verification mode

If the task is smoke test, integration verify, or `/verify-phase2`:

1. Run `./scripts/smoke-test.sh` and `./scripts/smoke-test-phase2.sh` before any Read of prior sessions
2. Load only `AGENTS.md` + relevant service `AGENTS.md`
3. See [docs/handoff-verification-agent.md](../docs/handoff-verification-agent.md)

## Do not read (implementation / verification)

Unless the user pasted a path for scoring:

- `~/.cursor/projects/**/agent-transcripts/**`
- `~/.cursor/projects/**/terminals/**` (use `Await` once; no double-Read)
- `evals/live-model/README.md`, `evals/live-model/manifest.json` â€” run scripts instead

## Do not re-read (same session)

Unless the user edited the file, you StrReplace'd it, or the task is harness/meta work:

- **Global:** `~/.cursor/HARNESS.md`, `~/.cursor/TOOLING.md`, `~/.cursor/memory/MEMORY.md`, `~/.cursor/rules/`, `~/.cursor/skills/**/SKILL.md`
- **Repo contract:** `AGENTS.md`, `docs/phase2-implementation-spec.md`, `docs/handoff-parallel-agent.md`, `docs/handoff-verification-agent.md`
- **Eval harness:** `scripts/score-agent-transcript.py`, `evals/live-model/README.md`, `evals/live-model/manifest.json` â€” run scripts instead of reading source

For `/token-efficiency`, `/live-eval`, and `/live-eval-phase2`: one Shell call to `./scripts/token-efficiency.sh`, `./scripts/run-live-evals.sh`, or `./scripts/run-live-evals-phase2.sh`; no Read of scorer/eval files.

